Anniversary of UNESCO commemorated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate signed articles to the 54th anniversary of UNESCO. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since its foundation, UNESCO has functioned in conformity with its mission and purpose, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Education and the international exchange of information have become brisk and energetic joint scientific researches are under way worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that investment in developing countries has increased and greater attention is being paid to the problems of these countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Some western countries, displeased with this, worked hard to control UNESCO activities under the pretext of the issue of its reform but their intention was frustrated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that on the occasion of the anniversary of UNESCO the DPRK estimates the efforts of UNESCO for human civilization and progress and hopes that UNESCO will achieve greater success in its efforts to attain its objective.

Seminar on Kim Jong Il's work held in Guyana
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- A seminar on General Secretary  Kim Jong Il's famous work "Socialism Is a Science" was held by the Group for the Study of Comrade Kim Jong Il's Works of the Amerindian Action Movement of Guyana and the Georgetown Group for the Study of Comrade Kim Jong Il's Works on October 26 and 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Robert Williams, chairman of the Guyanese National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea of Comrade Kim Il Sung, said at the seminar that Kim Jong Il in his work proved the truth that socialism is bound to triumph and clearly indicated the basic ways of achieving the victory of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's idea that it is the basic way of winning the victory of socialism to strengthen the driving force of revolution and increase its role is a scientific idea whose validity and truth have been proven through the protracted struggle of the popular masses and the practical experience of the Korean revolution, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Peter Persaud, chairman of the Group for the Study of Comrade Kim Jong Il's Works of the Amerindian Action Movement of Guyana, said that the world politicians and progressive people, who were left without any faith and hope for socialism, came to have firm conviction of the victory of socialism and a weapon of struggle when Kim Jong Il clarified that socialism is a science and it is bound to triumph.

Korea's army-first politics praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- Miguel Mejia, secretary general of the United Left Movement of Dominica, when interviewed by a KCNA reporter before his departure from here, highly appreciated the outstanding army-first revolutionary leadership of the great Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the moves of the imperialists to isolate and stifle the DPRK were totally scotched by his outstanding army-first politics and back home he would widely introduce the shining successes achieved by it under this army-first revolutionary leadership through media. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that 2000 is a year for the DPRK, he stressed that all the achievements made by the Korean people are a brilliant fruition of Kim Jong Il's outstanding army-first revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the international authority of the DPRK has risen higher than ever before, he pledged to make positive efforts for the opening of diplomatic relations between Dominica and the DPRK.

14th seminar on Yun I Sang music held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- The 14th seminar on Yun I Sang music was held at the Pyongyang International House of Culture yesterday . &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Song Sok Hwan, vice-Minister of Culture, officials concerned, music experts, artistes in the city, widow Ri Su Ja and her daughter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The seminar heard speeches made on the subjects "special feature of Yun I Sang music works," "on method of melodic expression in Yun I Sang music" and "mixed sound of four dos and its national character as noticed in music Konghu for harp and stringed instrument."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers profoundly explained and proved the idea, theme, style, variety and methods of expression in the music works created by Yun I Sang on behalf of history and highly praised his patriotic creative activities for the country's reunification and national unity.

Anniversary of naming Kim Il Sung class celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Beijing, November 2 (KCNA) -- Beijing Middle School no. 5 marked the 50th anniversary of naming a class of the school Kim Il Sung class. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting of pupils of the school decided to name a class Kim Il Sung class on November 2, 1950, in deep reverence for the President Kim Il Sung who brought the China-Korea friendship into bloom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A celebration meeting took place on Nov. 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present were Su Guang, vice-president of the Chinese People's Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were the DPRK ambassador to China and the members of the delegation of East Pyongyang Senior Middle School no. 1 of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A silk banner to Kim Il Sung class from Mao Zedong class of East Pyongyang Senior Middle School no. 1 was conveyed there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants saw an art performance given by pupils of Beijing Middle School no. 5.

Ri Je Ma and medicine on four-type constitution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- Members at the research institute of constitutional medicine of the General Hospital of Koryo Medicine in the DPRK strive to make a wider and deeper study of the medicine on four-type constitution, the constitutional theory native to Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The author of this theory was Ri Je Ma (1837-1900), a medical man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to his theory, each man or woman is different from his or her physical condition and their function of internal organs. So the method of treatment should be variant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the course of his study, he divided the persons' constitutions into four types - Taeyangin, Soyangin, Taeumin and Soumin - and on analysis of their formal and functional and temperamental characteristics such as external appearance, size of viscera, mentality, symptoms and reaction to drugs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this basis, the administration of medicine was decided. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to confirm physical constitution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Je Ma's medical theory gives a detailed explanation to physical make, form and personal appearance, the state of physiological function and mentality. It also explains the diseases of viscera and symptoms according to physical types and medicines to be applied. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His four methods of medical examination include the classification of physical conditions by looking hearing, asking and pressing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The experts and doctors at the General Hospital of Koryo Medicine, who developed the subjective and sentimental theory of classics into the objective and scientific method of classification, classified people in classical and morphological ways and by function diagnosis, blood-group examination and reaction to medicines. As a result, the rate of the successful diagnosis showed 90 per cent and the efficiency of administered medicines rose to 85 per cent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Based on such methods, the doctors diagnosed the diseases caused by the weak viscera and administered medicines to patients, which have resulted in the reduction of the period of recovery. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the basis of such success, the doctors work hard to develop four-physical condition-based medicine on a mass scale and make deep study of how to eliminate the sources of diseases.

Unconverted long-term prisoner's note
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- Unconverted long-term prisoner Sin In Yong issued a note titled "Leaving over 90 years old mother behind in south."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the note he said that he could not take with him his 93 years old mother when he was coming to the much longed-for DPRK after serving 32-year-long gruesome prison term. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One should endure such parting for the sake of the country and reunification because I came to the fold of the homeland where happiness and peace are guaranteed under the care of leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The strong belief in the great leaders of the revolution Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il made the unconverted long-term prisoners overcome all sorts of difficulties and remain true to their faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Just as trunks of all trees and stems of all plants in the world are stretched towards the sun, the hearts of the unconverted long-term prisoners always went out to Pyongyang and they worked hard to have a mental pabulum for their survival. We were not afraid of torture by the enemy but feared that our faith might be shaken. That was why we got works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il by all means and methods and avidly read them to train ourselves and deepen our faith.

Members of delegation of European Parliament interviewed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 4 (KCNA) -- Members of the delegation of the European Parliament headed by Jacques Santer, member of the parliament and ex-president of the European Union Commission, were interviewed by reporters at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The head of the delegation said that the purpose of its visit to the DPRK was to give further impetus to the detente and reconciliation process on the Korean peninsula following the adoption of the historic June 15 north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The European Union intends to make a positive contribution to giving greater momentum to the detente and peace process on the Korean peninsula in the future, too, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief aim of the delegation's visit is to qualitatively strengthen the bilateral relations between the European Union and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recalled that member states of the European union officially expressed their will to open diplomatic relations with the DPRK. Noting that the EU has a plan to render increased assistance to the DPRK, he hoped the dialogues between them would gain in depth in different fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing to the EU's plan to increase aid to activities of the Korean Peninsula Energy Development Organization (KEDO), he expressed his belief that the side of KEDO would fully implement its commitment under the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework.
